      <h1>ParkerPixiePaws — Cozy Amigurumi</h1>

      <!-- Polished blurb -->
      <p><strong>I stitch soft, plush, whimsical friends that feel like a hug.</strong> Amigurumi is more than yarn and hooks — it’s a craft rooted in Japanese tradition, patience, and the joy of gifting. Many makers speak of a little “spirit” in handmade things — the warmth of the hands that shaped them.</p>
      <p>For me, it’s both therapy and expression: a way to honor the people who inspire, teach, and comfort me; to stitch metaphors into every piece; and to turn yarn into lasting symbols of friendship and love. Each creation has a backstory — a reason it came to be. Through this storybook adventure, I’m inviting you to wander with me and witness <em>healing through art.</em></p>

