<!-- BONNIE (image left, text right) -->
<section class="entry" id="bonnie">
  <div class="row">
    <figure class="media reveal-up">
      <img src="/img/Bonnie.jpg" alt="Bonnie the chicken amigurumi" />
    </figure>
    <article class="copy reveal-up">
      <div class="kicker">Chicken · Humor & Resilience</div>
      <h2>Bonnie: Humor & Resilience</h2>
      <p>Bonnie has the wildest origin story of them all. She was supposed to be my “Trojan chicken.” The plan was dark and raw: crochet a chicken beautiful enough for my mother to proudly display, then fill it with slips of paper — my hurts, my rage, my childhood wounds. I was going to hand it to her, let her cut it open, and finally see all I’d carried. My counselor gently suggested there might be better ways to heal from childhood PTSD.</p>
      <p>So Bonnie transformed. She became something else, someone else’s. Instead of being a Trojan horse for pain, she became a tribute for a friend whose honesty, humor, and grounding presence has been a lifeline in my recovery. This “chicken lady” fills her home with warmth and resilience, and she’s far more worthy of such a gift than my mother ever was. Bonnie isn’t trauma anymore — she’s testimony.</p>
      <div class="caption">
        <p><em>Bonnie the chicken amigurumi.</em></p>
        <p><em>Bonnie — once a Trojan plan, now a tribute to honest friendship.</em></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
